l theory and practice throughout the early modern period. Expertly translated by Carolyn Guile and featuring an introduction that explores Polish Enlightenment architectural writing as an example of cultural exchange, inheritance, and transformation, this edition of Potocki’s treatise broadens our understanding of European architectural history during the early modern period.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 0aArchitecturevEarly works to 1800. 0aArchitecturexEarly works to 1800xPoland. 0aArchitecturezPolandvEarly works to 1800. 7aARCHITECTURE / History / Baroque & Rococo.2bisacsh  aArchitectural history.  aArchitectural theory.  aEighteenth-century architecture.  aIgnacy Potocki.  aPartitions of Poland.  aPoland.  aPolish architecture.  aStanis aw Kostka Potocki.1 aGuile, Carolyn C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311074525240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780271070544?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271070544423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780271070544/original  a978-3-11-074525-2  Penn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_AD  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK